  "text": "Additional supporting evidence for a role for PKC in myogenic signaling was provided by the observation that diacylglycerol accumulates in cannulated renal arcuate arteries following an increase in intraluminal pressure [CITATION_1] . Diacylglycerol is required in the physiological activation of a number of the PKC isozymes. From the temporal data provided in that study, it is difficult to determine with any certainty whether the activation of PKC in renal vessels would be consistent with a role in contractile function or whether activation of the kinase may be a reflection of other cellular processes initiated by the mechanical stimulus, such as a growth response.",
